			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon Affininty<a name="25707"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 5 04 11:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think what he meant by &quot;weapons have a fixed proc rate&quot; is that with maxed Dex, the weapon procs at a fixed rate of roughly X times per minute (X varies from weapon to weapon, with most of them sitting around 2).
<br />

<br />
This just means that haste or other stats do not affect the proc rate...which is determined by the weapon, WA, and dex only.
<br />

<br />
From personal experience (as well as confirmation I've found from other threads/boards), dex does affect proc rate and seems to fairly linearly.  Having a dex of 285 seems to cause procs to happen almost 50% more often for me as opposed to my unbuffed 203 dex.  Procs in the offhand do seems to occur less often, but I think that is due to the offhand not swinging as often.  Procs can happen even on misses, so they seem to be tied to how often the weapon is swung...not how often it connects.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Cinge Silver'Song, Maestro of 65 Songs</span></td>
