			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon Affininty<a name="25749"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 5 04 2:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As I understand it (from reading previous discussions), procs work on a &quot;time since last proc&quot; system. The longer that it has been since a given proc has gone off, the greater the chance that the weapon will proc on the next swing (also modified by dex, WA etc). Over time, this produces a proc rate which is independent of attack speed. However, you can still theoretically proc on every swing, but the chances of this are low (which is why strings of consecutive procs are relatively rare).
<br />

<br />
Additionally, multiple procs are handled independently, and the proc chance on the offhand is modified downward (also independent of attack speed).
<br />

<br />
Miiri</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
