				<td colspan="2"><span>But people are missing the point -- you won't get more procs in 1 minute's time by slowing yourself.  You will get the SAME NUMBER whether you are slowed or hasted over the same period of time.  Yes, the proc rate per swing goes up when you're slowed, but not because you're procing more -- because you're swinging less.
<br />

<br />
If you are in range of the mob and have attack on, it matters not HOW OFTEN you swing the weapon or how often you hit.  The proc rate per unit of TIME is fixed.
<br />

<br />
My level 11 ranger with a 2-hand hammer from Kael that procs some cold DD was getting procs every 30 seconds with the d*mn thing even though his 2hb skill was 0 and he was never hitting anything with it and swinging slower than molasses.</span></td>
