				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon Affininty<a name="27816"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 1:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Most weapons have a mainhand base proc rate somewhere around 1.5 to 2 procs per minute. This applies to both one handed and two handed weapons. Baring a modified proc rate such as what you find on the cleric summoned hammers (which proc somewhere around 630% base), this is the standard.
<br />

<br />
Of course, this problem with this is understanding is how the offhand effects this. If proc rate is constant over time and not over swings, why do weapons in the offhand have a lower proc rate than those in the mainhand? Theoretically, even though the offhand is attacking less, proc rates should be similar.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">&nbsp;&nbsp;Hunter Sirioh <br>
