			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon Affininty<a name="27891"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 5:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I know this (semi)disagrees with what some other people have said, but proc rate is tied to both time and weapon swings.  The proc RATE is tied to time as has been multiply described above...however, it actually performs the check on a per-swing basis.  Since the offhand weapon swings less, the proc check is done less often, and the proc goes off less often as well.
<br />

<br />
That is why warriors with the earthshaker see such impressive effects when slowed...the system sees oh, they are only swinging 1.5 times per minute, so they should proc 66% of the time (or something similar to that).  Then, when the warrior kicks in their AE rampage discipline, the timer check still sees 70% slow, and thinks 66% of swings should proc, even though the warrior is swinging it 80 times (once for each mob in the swarm in front of him)...hence getting 50-60 procs in about 3 seconds.
<br />

<br />
I hope this makes sense.  I've seen it in action, so this descriptions seems to best match in-game experience.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Cinge Silver'Song, Maestro of 65 Songs</span></td>
