			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapon Affininty<a name="30454"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 25 04 9:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Try this. Watch a lvl 65 cleric with maxed out dex swinging on a mob with a high end hammer with Hand of the God proc. What you tend to see is on the first mob the cleric will proc numberous times very quickly. Then it won't proc at all for awhile. Then you might get a few procs or a small burst of them. What happens is the proc rate is very high but quickly bumps up against the max procs/minute ceiling. Then the hammer stops procing for a time. Once enough time has lapsed and the cleric is under the max proc/minute ceiling the hammer starts procing again but will often very quickly max out again. This causes the hammer to stop procing again and actually spaces out procs a fair amount. 
<br />

<br />
What alot of clerics do is swing with their weapon till they get a burst of procs then nuke a few times. This maximizes their DPS (what little we have). 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
